      "id": 100,
      "options": {
        "content": "# Drive9 Performance Control Room\n\nThis dashboard is optimized for performance triage, not for broad business observability.\n\n1. Start with the top cards to spot the dominant signal: throughput, latency, saturation, or errors.\n2. Use **Request Path** when users report slowness or API instability.\n3. Use **Application Workload** when HTTP looks normal but backend execution gets slower.\n4. Use **Database Pressure** when latency climbs together with waits, pool saturation, or slower DB operations.\n\nFilters let you narrow the view by route, component, operation, DB role, DB operation, and API event.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Guide",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
